<subSubSection id="13886529FF8FFFA957493D4B812B76E3" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5B2D36A2FF8FFFA957493D4B87F47623" blockId="15.[834,1475,573,1845]" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA957493D4B87DB7343" bold="true" box="[835,947,573,597]" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Remarks.</emphasis>
Species herein referred to 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA950ED3D4B81E37343" authority="Ahyong, 2018" authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2018" box="[1255,1419,573,597]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Discorsotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA950ED3D4B81E37343" box="[1255,1419,573,597]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Discorsotheres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="72D557CBFF8FFFA9519F3D4B87E97363" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" rank="genus">new genus</taxonomicNameLabel>
are removed from 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA9505D3D2B80867363" box="[1111,1262,605,629]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Ostracotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA9505D3D2B80867363" box="[1111,1262,605,629]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Ostracotheres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of the subquadrate (versus rounded) carapace, the slender (versus robust) chelipeds with broadened occlusal surfaces, and asymmetrical pereopod 3 (versus symmetrical in length and structure). An asymmetrical pereopod 3 is also known from 
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA957883D8B80777203" box="[898,1055,765,789]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Amussiotheres</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3F034B53FF8FFFA950233D8B80B27203" author="Ng PKL &amp; Ho PH" box="[1065,1242,765,789]" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" pagination="740 - 751" refId="ref31003" refString="Ng PKL &amp; Ho PH (2016) A new genus for Fabia obtusidentata Dai, Feng, Song and Chen, 1980, a pea crab (Decapoda: Brachyura: Pinnotheridae) symbiotic with the moon scallop Amusium pleuronectes (Linnaeus, 1758) (Mollusca: Pectinidae). Journal of Crustacean Biology, 36: 740 - 751." type="journal article" year="2016">Ng &amp; Ho, 2016</bibRefCitation>
(Indo-West Pacific), 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA957493C6B80F67223" authority="Campos, 2009" authorityName="Campos" authorityYear="2009" box="[835,1182,797,821]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Enigmatheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA957493C6B878E7223" box="[835,998,797,821]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Enigmatheres</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3F034B53FF8FFFA957F83C6B80F67223" author="Campos E" box="[1010,1182,797,821]" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" pagination="29 - 44" refId="ref28580" refString="Campos E (2009) A new species and two new genera of pinnotherid crabs from the northeastern Pacific Ocean, with a reappraisal of the subfamily Pinnotherinae de Haan, 1833 (Crustacea: Brachyura: Pinnotheridae). Zootaxa, 2022: 29 - 44." type="journal article" year="2009">Campos, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(eastern Pacific), some American species currently assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA950D33C4B81FB7243" authority="Dana, 1851" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1851" box="[1241,1427,829,853]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Fabia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA950D33C4B81707243" box="[1241,1304,829,853]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Fabia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3F034B53FF8FFFA951163C4B81FB7243" author="Dana JD" box="[1308,1427,829,853]" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" pagination="283 - 291" refId="ref28753" refString="Dana JD (1851) On the classification of the Crustacea Grapsoidea. American Journal of Science and Arts, (2) 12: 283 - 291." type="journal article" year="1851">Dana, 1851</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="3F034B53FF8FFFA957493C2B878B7263" author="Campos E" box="[835,995,861,885]" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" pagination="556 - 563" refId="ref28544" refString="Campos E (1996) Partial revision of pinnotherid crab genera with a two-segmented palp on the third maxilliped (Decapoda: Brachyura). Journal of Crustacean Biology, 16: 556 - 563." type="journal article" year="1996">Campos, 1996</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA957F23C2B812C7263" authority="Ng &amp; Ngo, 2010" authorityName="Ng &amp; Ngo" authorityYear="2010" box="[1016,1348,861,885]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Solenotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA957F23C2B80EA7263" box="[1016,1154,861,885]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Solenotheres</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3F034B53FF8FFFA950813C2B812C7263" author="Ng PKL &amp; Ngo VT" box="[1163,1348,861,885]" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" pagination="61 - 68" refId="ref31119" refString="Ng PKL &amp; Ngo VT (2010) Solenotheres prolixus, a new genus and new species of pinnotherid crab (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura) associated with the razor clam, Solen corneus Lamarck, 1818 (Solenidae) in Vietnam. Zootaxa, 2570: 61 - 68." type="journal article" year="2010">Ng &amp; Ngo, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="23857632FF8FFFA9515F3C2B81DF7263" box="[1365,1463,861,885]" name="Vietnam" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA9577E3C08800B7283" authority="Rathbun, 1900" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1900" box="[884,1123,893,917]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Zaops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA9577E3C0887DE7283" box="[884,950,894,917]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Zaops</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3F034B53FF8FFFA957CA3C0B800B7283" author="Rathbun MJ" box="[960,1123,893,917]" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" pagination="583 - 592" refId="ref31972" refString="Rathbun MJ (1900) The catametopous or grapsoid crabs of North America. American Naturalist, 34: 583 - 592." type="journal article" year="1900">Rathbun, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(western Atlantic) – all genera with a 3-segmented maxilliped 3 palp. Among pinnotherids with a 2-segmented maxilliped 3 palp, however, pereopod 3 asymmetry is unique to 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA950413CAB808472E3" authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2018" box="[1099,1260,989,1013]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Discorsotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA950413CAB808472E3" box="[1099,1260,989,1013]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Discorsotheres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA951163CAB81D472E3" authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2018" box="[1308,1468,989,1013]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Discorsotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA951163CAB81D472E3" box="[1308,1468,989,1013]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Discorsotheres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the pereopod 3 of one side (usually the right) is similar in form to pereopods 2 and 4. The opposite pereopod 3, however, is typically more elongated, with the propodus usually slightly expanded distally and with the dactylus more elongated and with a less curved, sometimes reduced tip. The flexor margin of the propodus and dactylus of the longer pereopod 3 is distinctly more setose than on the opposite pereopod 3 (e.g., 
<figureCitation id="C3A92A27FF8FFFA9509D3BAB817B75E3" box="[1175,1299,1245,1269]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[136,171,1531,1553]" captionTargetBox="[137,1476,192,1513]" captionTargetId="figure-8@17.[131,1477,189,1524]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 9. Discorsotheres subglobosus (Baker, 1907) new combination. A–G, female lectotype, cl 10.6 mm, cw 12.4 mm, Gulf St. Vincent, AM P151; H–I, ovigerous female paralectotype, cl 8.7 mm, cw 9.9 mm, Gulf St. Vincent, AM P102300; J–K, ovigerous female, cl 8.6 mm, cw 10.5 mm, Edithburgh, AM P64673; L–M, ovigerous female, cl 7.3 mm, cw 8.9 mm, Edithburgh, AM P64673; N–O, females, cl 7.8 cw 8.4, cl 7.8 cw 9.5 mm, Seacliff reef, SAM C12812. A, dorsal habitus; B, carapace, anterior view; C, carapace, right lateral view; D, cephalothorax, anterior view; E, right maxilliped 3; F, right chela, anterior view; G, right cheliped pollex, oblique anterior view; H, J, L, left pereopod 3; I, K, M, right pereopod 3; N, O, carapace frontal margin, dorsal view. Scale: A–C, H–M = 4.0 mm; D–F, N, O = 2.0 mm; G = 1.0." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5359757" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5359757/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Fig. 9H–M</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C3A92A27FF8FFFA9512B3BAB81DE75E3" box="[1313,1462,1245,1269]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[113,148,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[114,1452,265,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-7@20.[108,1458,258,1855]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 10. Discorsotheres camposi new species. A–M, female holotype, cl 10.8 mm, cw 10.3 mm, Tonga, ZRC 2003.0299; N–Q, ovigerous female paratype, cl 12.9 mm, cw 14.0 mm, Lifou, MNHN-IU-2017-11712; R–T, ovigerous female paratype, cl 15.3 mm, cw 16.4 mm, Caroline Islands, USNM 104989; U–W, ovigerous female paratype, cl 14.9 mm, cw 17.5 mm, Caroline Islands, USNM 104989. A, dorsal habitus; B, carapace, anterior view; C, carapace, right lateral view; D, cephalothorax, anterior view; E, right maxilliped 3; F, right chela, anterior view; G–I, left pereopods 2–4; J–M, right pereopods 2–5; N, left cheliped pollex, oblique anterior view; O, R, U, carapace anterior margin, dorsal view; P, S, V, left pereopod 3 dactylus &amp; propodus; Q, T, W, right pereopod 3 dactylus &amp; propodus. Scale: A–C, G–M, O–W = 2.0 mm; D–F = 1.0 mm; N = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5359759" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5359759/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">10H, L, P, Q</figureCitation>
). The function of such asymmetry is not known, although a similar asymmetry is also exhibited by 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA950E63A6B811E7423" authorityName="Ng &amp; Ngo" authorityYear="2010" box="[1260,1398,1309,1333]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Solenotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA950E63A6B811E7423" box="[1260,1398,1309,1333]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Solenotheres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Aside from the 2- rather than 3-segmented maxilliped 3 palp, the proportionally narrower carapace, and broadened rather than narrow cheliped finger tips, 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA950703A0B81737483" authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2018" box="[1146,1307,1405,1429]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Discorsotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA950703A0B81737483" box="[1146,1307,1405,1429]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Discorsotheres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA957573AEB878E74A3" authorityName="Ng &amp; Ngo" authorityYear="2010" box="[861,998,1437,1461]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Solenotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA957573AEB878E74A3" box="[861,998,1437,1461]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Solenotheres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA950563AE880F574A3" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1900" box="[1116,1181,1438,1461]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Zaops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA950563AE880F574A3" box="[1116,1181,1438,1461]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Zaops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(host 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA950D13AEB878D74C3" authority="(Gmelin, 1791)" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1791" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Crassostrea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="virginica">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA950D13AEB81A974A3" box="[1243,1473,1437,1461]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Crassostrea virginica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3F034B53FF8FFFA957433ACB87B574C3" author="Gmelin JF" box="[841,989,1469,1493]" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" pagination="3021 - 3910" refId="ref29201" refString="Gmelin JF (1791) Vermes. In: Gmelin JF (ed.) Caroli a Linnaei Systema Naturae per Regna Tria Naturae, Ed. 10. Tome 1 (6). G. E. Beer, Lipsiae [Leipzig]. Pp. 3021 - 3910." type="book chapter" year="1791">Gmelin, 1791</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA957E73ACB803B74C3" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[1005,1107,1469,1493]" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Ostreidae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA950803ACB814A74C3" box="[1162,1314,1469,1493]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Amussiotheres</emphasis>
(host 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA951553ACB871A74E2" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Amusium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA951553ACB81A974C2" box="[1375,1473,1469,1492]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Amusium</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA957753AAB816074E3" authority="(Gmelin, 1791)" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1791" box="[895,1288,1501,1525]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Ylistrum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="japonicum">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA957753AAB803C74E3" box="[895,1108,1501,1525]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Ylistrum japonicum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3F034B53FF8FFFA9506F3AAB816874E3" author="Gmelin JF" box="[1125,1280,1501,1525]" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" pagination="3021 - 3910" refId="ref29201" refString="Gmelin JF (1791) Vermes. In: Gmelin JF (ed.) Caroli a Linnaei Systema Naturae per Regna Tria Naturae, Ed. 10. Tome 1 (6). G. E. Beer, Lipsiae [Leipzig]. Pp. 3021 - 3910." type="book chapter" year="1791">Gmelin, 1791</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA9511C3AAB81EF74E3" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[1302,1415,1501,1525]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Pectinidae</taxonomicName>
) also have an asymmetrical pereopod 3, the asymmetry is expressed principally in significant elongation of the leg of one side, with a straight, largely glabrous dactylus; both of these genera have a 3-segmented maxilliped 3 palp and show little similarity to either 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA9504F390B808E7783" authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2018" box="[1093,1254,1661,1685]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Discorsotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA9504F390B808E7783" box="[1093,1254,1661,1685]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Discorsotheres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA95103390B81FB7783" authorityName="Ng &amp; Ngo" authorityYear="2010" box="[1289,1427,1661,1685]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Solenotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA95103390B81FB7783" box="[1289,1427,1661,1685]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Solenotheres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. All species of 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA957BB39EB803A77A3" authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2018" box="[945,1106,1693,1717]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Discorsotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA957BB39EB803A77A3" box="[945,1106,1693,1717]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Discorsotheres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur in the Indo-West Pacific and have discrete distributions in the Persian Gulf (
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA9513239C881DA77C3" authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Nobili" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1336,1458,1725,1749]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Ostracotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spondyli">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA9513239C881DA77C3" box="[1336,1458,1725,1749]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">D. spondyli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), southern 
<collectingCountry id="23857632FF8FFFA957A239AB806277E3" box="[936,1034,1757,1781]" name="Australia" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA9501139A880A977E3" authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Baker" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[1051,1217,1757,1781]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Pinnotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subglobosus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA9501139A880A977E3" box="[1051,1217,1757,1781]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">D. subglobosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), northeastern Asia (
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA951A239A887BC7603" authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Sakai" baseAuthorityYear="1939" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Ostracotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subquadratus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA951A239A887BC7603" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">D. subquadratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the tropical western Pacific (
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA9514A398881D17603" authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2018" box="[1344,1465,1790,1813]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Discorsotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camposi">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA9514A398881D17603" box="[1344,1465,1790,1813]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">D. camposi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="C3A92A27FF8FFFA95741386B87E67623" box="[843,910,1821,1845]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[112,147,978,1000]" captionTargetBox="[111,1451,190,963]" captionTargetId="figure-565@16.[91,1466,177,966]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 8. Distribution of species of Discorsotheres new genus. (■) D. camposi new species; (●) D. spondyli (Nobili, 1905) new combination; (▲) D. subglobosus (Baker, 1907) new combination; (▼) D. subquadratus (Sakai, 1939) new combination." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5359755" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5359755/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B2D36A2FF8FFFA95749382B812B76E3" blockId="15.[835,1475,1885,2037]" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">
Identification of species of 
<taxonomicName id="9C924D21FF8FFFA95066382B81657663" authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2018" box="[1132,1293,1885,1909]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Discorsotheres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69E6EAB0FF8FFFA95066382B81657663" box="[1132,1293,1885,1909]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="553">Discorsotheres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
relies in part on the dorsal carapace ornamentation. Owing to the soft carapace of most species of the genus, poor preservation can overaccentuate the prominence of the median swelling, so care should be taken in identifying such specimens.
</paragraph>
